<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1873-12-03T11:14:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1873-12-03T11:14:00-05:00" n="674" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d674">
                            <head>No. 672.<lb/><hi rend="italic">General <persName type="from">Sickles</persName> to Mr. <persName type="to">Fish</persName>.</hi></head>
                            <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Madrid</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1873-12-03T16:00:00-00:14"><hi rend="italic">December</hi> 3, 1873—4 p.m.</date> (Received Dec.
                                    3.)</dateline></opener>
                            <p>Your instruction of yesterday received at 11 this morning. Minister
                                of state informs me at 4 this afternoon that orders have been sent
                                to Spanish minister in Washington for the execution of the
                                stipulations of the protocol of the 29th ultimo relative to the
                                surrender of the vessel.</p>
                            <closer><signed>SICKLES.</signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>